  <div class="news-row">
	<div class="news-row">
    <div class="news-row-left"><img src="news_and_events/News Highlights/Consortium_ProfWang.jpg" width="115" height="82" /></div>
    <div class="news-row-right">
      <h2>NUS to form an International Engineering Science Consortium with Osaka University, KTH, University of California, Berkeley and University of Toronto.</h2>
      <p>NUS is in a strong position to take a leadership role in the multidisciplinary engineering science arena.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="news_and_events/News/2013 news/International Engineering Science Consortium.pdf" target="new">here</a> for more details</p>
    </div>
    <div class="clear"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="news-row">
    <div class="news-row-left"><img src="news_and_events/News Highlights/HydrogenProduction_Ernest.jpg" /></div>
    <div class="news-row-right">
      <h2>Rooftop hydrogen production system at block EA</h2>
      <p>The NUS team led by ESP Associate Ernest Chua has discovered a very cost-effective way of producing high-quality hydrogen which is an important element for clean and sustainable energy. The hydrogen production system splits water by using a combination of electrolysis, photocatalysis and photovoltaic panels.</p>
    <p>Click <a href="news_and_events/News/2013 news/Rooftop hydrogen production system at block EA.pdf" target="new">here</a> for more details</p>
    </div>
